This example runs the same ICs as in examples/IsolateddSph_cups/ with PartType7 instead of PartType1. 

In run.sh, the simulation is run for one timestep and tests whether the SPH density for SIDM particles agrees with the analytical NFW profile used to generate the ICs.

In run_with_gas.sh, the ICs are duplicated for PartType0 and run for one timestep. The gas densities are then compared to the SIDM densities. This script assumes you have already run run.sh.